name: Volunteers of America Los Angeles
review_text: For a faith based organization, this place can be evil and unethical at times. Someone got beat up at the Boyle heights shelter and staff just stood there and watched, one of them even laughed. Sad

name: Volunteers of America Los Angeles
review_text:
Very disappointed with organizations that are funded I was referred to VOA by Hopic another organization that refer people who are homeless from all walks and backgrounds the VOA facility for women in Los Angeles CA on Avalon Avenue was very clean however the staffs people and communication skills  towards the women was very poor the women are human beings who should be treated with care and concern I am currently up under a neurol surgeon and primary doctor's care for a cervical spine condition I brought this issue to both organizations during intake I requested
for a pillow to dupport my neck and explain to the staffs and my assigned case manager of my condition I was told by staffs that I needed something in writing to be accommodated after providing documentation I was still denied a pill to support my neck while sleeping no one should ever be denied accommodation for a medical condition I am calling upon the CEO of the VOA organization to please put some policies in place for th men and women who have disabilities. Thank you

name: Volunteers of America Los Angeles
review_text: If you do not have good credit and earn 2.7 times the amount of rent required at each Apt. location applied to? you will not qualify in the state of California. You will then be offered a room in a house with several other people at best.  In the meantime, this organization will continue to receive funding by accepting you into their program and in turn, providing you little or nothing in return. My advice? Seek assistance from another program or directly from the V.A.

review_text: The people there are very helpful and full of pleasantries. I felt such a comforting sensation with the service that I look forward to my next visit.

name: Volunteers of America Los Angeles
review_text:
Yep, my experience WAS the same... All too typical stereotype of public services literally "low budget" operations! Staff earns minimal $, with must be shallow training as well and that's the level of customer service... Minimal/Shallow. Poor customer; Poor value. BUT HERES THE THING... I was a homeless vet and had decided to DO THE MOST with the services provided and guess what? My experience with V of A became a blessing! Got decent housing, access to good jobs and ^ in my mental & physical health... V of A was an asset that aided me TO HELP MY SELF (!) once I decided thats what they are! Positive attitude is EVERYTHANG!!!

name: Volunteers of America Los Angeles
review_text: If I could give this organization zero stars, I would. Just like so many veteran organizations, if you're not at the bottom of the barrel, you're at the bottom of the list. Translation? It caters to the drug addict and criminal veterans. If you are drug free and have a clean record and an honorable discharge, this is NOT the place for you.
